                          Guildcraft

    Guildcraft lets guild members consume saved profession materials for
guild-themed preparations. These preparations support guild roleplay,
guild command hooks, and material demand loops.

Commands:
  guildcraft list
  guildcraft <guild> <use>

Examples:
  guildcraft bard strings
  guildcraft ninja smoke bomb
  guildcraft mage scribing ink
  guildcraft cleric incense
  guildcraft ranger poultice
  guildcraft druid verdant bundle

    Each preparation consumes saved materials from your profession storage
and sets a timed preparation on you. If you do not belong to the matching
guild, the preparation is refused.

    Druids, Bards, Ninjas, Mages, Clerics, Paladins, and Rangers all have
starter reagent uses. Use guildcraft list to see the current catalog.

Getting started:
  1. Use 'guildcraft list' to see the current guild material uses.
  2. Use 'reagents search <item>' when you need source hints.
  3. Gather the materials through professions, workers, monster reagents,
     fishing, or work-order rewards.
  4. Use 'guildcraft <guild> <use>' while in the matching guild.
